 of their father. </span><span class=\"v4_36_7\"><sup id=\"Num.36.7\" class=\"v4_36_7\">7</sup>The inheritance of the people of Israel shall not be transferred from one tribe to another, for every one of the people of Israel shall hold on to the inheritance of the tribe of his fathers. </span><span class=\"v4_36_8\"><sup id=\"Num.36.8\" class=\"v4_36_8\">8</sup>And every daughter who possesses an inheritance in any tribe of the people of Israel shall be wife to one of the clan of the tribe of her father, so that every one of the people of Israel may possess the inheritance of his fathers. </span><span class=\"v4_36_9\"><sup id=\"Num.36.9\" class=\"v4_36_9\">9</sup>So no inheritance shall be transferred from one tribe to another, for each of the tribes of the people of Israel shall hold on to its own inheritance.\u2019\u201d</span></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"v4_36_10\"><sup id=\"Num.36.10\" class=\"v4_36_10\">10</sup>The daughters of Zelophehad did as the <span class=\"nd\">Lord</span> commanded Moses, </span><span class=\"v4_36_11\"><sup id=\"Num.36.11\" class=\"v4_36_11\">11</sup>for Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, were married to sons of their father\u2019s brothers. </span><span class=\"v4_36_12\"><sup id=\"Num.36.12\" class=\"v4_36_12\">12</sup>They were married into the clans of the people of Manasseh the son of Joseph, and their inheritance remained in the tribe of their father\u2019s clan.</span></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"v4_36_13\"><sup id=\"Num.36.13\" class=\"v4_36_13\">13</sup>These are the commandments and the rules that the <span class=\"nd\">Lord</span> commanded through Moses to the people of Israel in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho.</span></p>\n</div>\n", 
